What did you accomplish yesterday?: Each team member provides a brief update on the tasks they completed the previous day.

What will you work on today?: Each team member shares their plans for the day, including the tasks they will be working on.

Are there any obstacles or challenges?: If any team members are facing roadblocks or challenges that are hindering their progress, they can raise them during the meeting to seek assistance or support.

Do you need any help from the team?: If a team member requires assistance or collaboration from their colleagues, they can ask for it during this time.

Is there anything that may affect the sprint goal?: If there are any issues, risks, or changes that may impact the overall sprint goal, they can be discussed in the meeting.
